    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7, then boil half a kettle</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into chips</p><p>Add the <strong>chips</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/macsween-haggis-burger-with-black-pepper-mayo-and-chips/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>panko breadcrumbs </strong>to a bowl with 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[65ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[85ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and mix it all together until all the water has been absorbed</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/macsween-haggis-burger-with-black-pepper-mayo-and-chips/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Crumble your <strong>haggis </strong>into the bowl with the soaked breadcrumbs and give everything a good mix up until thoroughly combined (clean hands is the best way!)</p><p>Divide and shape into 1 patty per person \u2013 this is your <strong>haggis patty[ies]</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/macsween-haggis-burger-with-black-pepper-mayo-and-chips/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>cracked black pepper </strong>and <strong>mayo</strong> in a small bowl \u2013 this is your <strong>black pepper mayo</strong></p><p>Wash your<strong> lettuce</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper and roughly shred</p><p>Slice your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> into rounds</p><p>Peel and slice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong> into rings</p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/macsween-haggis-burger-with-black-pepper-mayo-and-chips/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add your<strong> brioche halves</strong> to the pan, cut-side down, and cook for 2-3 min or until golden</p><p>Once golden, transfer to a plate and set aside for later, reserve the pan</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/macsween-haggis-burger-with-black-pepper-mayo-and-chips/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once the pan is hot, add the<strong> haggis patty[ies] </strong>to the pan, press down firmly with a spatula and cook for 4-5 min on one side or until browned</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/macsween-haggis-burger-with-black-pepper-mayo-and-chips/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once browned, flip the<strong> haggis patty[ies]</strong>, then top with the <strong>grated cheese</strong> and cook, covered, for 4-5 min further or until the cheese has melted and the haggis patty[ies] are cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>cheesy haggis burger[s]</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 5? You may need to do this in batches!</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/macsween-haggis-burger-with-black-pepper-mayo-and-chips/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>To build your burger, spread the <strong>black pepper mayo </strong>on the <strong>toasted brioche base</strong>, then top with a handful of <strong>shredded lettuce</strong>, <strong>tomato rounds</strong>, <strong>shallot rings </strong>and the <strong>cheesy haggis burger</strong></p><p>Top with a <strong>toasted brioche lid </strong>and serve with the <strong>chips </strong>and <strong>remaining shredded lettuce </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
